-- Paulson & Co. Maintains Position in SPDR Gold Trust
-- B y   D e b a r a t i   R o y
-- 2012-05-15T21:22:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-15/paulson-co-maintains-position-in-spdr-gold-trust.html
Paulson & Co., the hedge fund founded
by billionaire  John Paulson , maintained its stake in the SPDR
Gold Trust during the first quarter, according to a government
filing.  As of March 31, Paulson held 17.3 million shares in the
exchange-traded product backed by the precious metal, unchanged
from the end of the fourth quarter, a U.S. Securities and
Exchange Commission filing showed today.  The SPDR Trust is the biggest exchange-traded product
backed by gold.  To contact the reporter on this story:
